\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i0 In the Course in Miracles Jesus\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s voice is giving us insights on how to train our mind to fit into the world the world according to the Urantia book tells instead of the world we currently live in. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i0 The Urantia book expands on our current knowledge of the world we think we know. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\i0 In this book we will make a few monumental assumptions. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\i0 1. The first assumption is that the voice of Jesus dictated the Course in Miracles. Helen Schuman, the scribe of the Course in Miracles, claimed to hear a kind of nonverbal communication. This nonverbal voice identified himself as Jesus. She spent (check fact) 7 years taking shorthand notes each evening from the nonverbal voice. Her notes were edited many times until Helen and her partner in this endeavor Bill Thetford, arrived at an final edited version they felt comfortable with. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\i0 The version of the CIM, completed in cooperation by Helen and Bill, will be used as reference in this book. This version predates the popular version of the CIM published by FIP. The Helen and Bill version contains additional pertinent information that was edited out of the FIP version. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\i0    2. The second assumption we make is that the claim of origin of the Urantia book is also accurate.  Jesus as creator, did also approve of another book to be provided by his subordinates  and associates. This book claims to be a major revelation of expanded cosmology. The Urantia book claims to be authored by a wide variety celestial beings, including angels and those beings of close association to the trinity itself. The book provides an enormous amount of information about our history, current standing in creation, the structure of creation, and our destiny and purpose. }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://035BE120-06A2-491F-BCF1-954CFCE831F4"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs26\i0 One fact to keep in mind is that our world was quarantined long ago by our celestial family due to a series of unfortunate events. At some point in the distant future this quarantine will be lifted and we will be able to rejoin our celestial family. }}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\i0 The claim that the Course in Miracles was dictated by the voice of Jesus will never be proven as a fact. Likewise, the claim of the Urantia book being authored by celestial beings will never be proven. However, I do think you will be amazed by the remarkable coincidence of how the concepts within the Course in Miracles complement the Urantia book, both of which have distinct and unique stories of origin. The fact that these two books of different origin fit so well together should give some level of proof of something extraordinary occurring in and of itself. }
\par\plain {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://5F4F436B-9DA7-4691-9F66-005960764D7D"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs26\i0 What would be the motivations of those who participated in the creation of these two books? Helen and Bill received no compensation from their participation in making the Course in Miracles a reality. Likewise, those involved in the publishing of the Urantia book received little attention or compensation. Both teams took many years to bring these books into being. Neither created a religious empire from them as previous religions did. }}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\i0 These two assumptions cannot be proven. However, what you may find striking is the synergy between these two books. They complement each other well. The complexity within these books are high. Yet a deep dive into the  major concepts show quite striking similarities, }
